<node id="Wine Packaging Methods">
  <data key="d0">Wine Packaging Methods</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The academic report explores different wine packaging methods and their impacts on wine preservation, sensory quality, economics, and sustainability.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08f3f1c8d96e46fade5e0b44bfa52840</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775588735</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Natural Cork">
  <data key="d0">Natural Cork</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Natural cork is used as a wine bottle closure and is the most expensive per-unit closure in the wine industry.&lt;SEP&gt;Natural cork is a traditional wine closure with variable oxygen transmission rates, affecting wine preservation and sensory outcomes.&lt;SEP&gt;Natural Cork is a traditional wine bottle stopper known for TCA risk but better aging capacity compared to synthetic alternatives.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08f3f1c8d96e46fade5e0b44bfa52840&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2eb65b8154604ecd58b709ac758de03&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bf37b81d72a72b3c8a73e22a2f838b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca4e8a21b5cc7aa7758c6cb466cdece6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775588735</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Screw Cap">
  <data key="d0">Screw Cap</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Screw caps, also known as Stelvin or ROPP closures, are wine bottle closures that use aluminum caps and liners to seal bottles.&lt;SEP&gt;Screw caps are wine closures with consistent oxygen transmission rates, used for aromatic white wines and early-drinking styles.&lt;SEP&gt;Screw Cap is a type of wine closure noted for its initial efficacy but with concerns over long-term viability due to liner brittleness.&lt;SEP&gt;A screw cap is a type of bottle closure that provides a seal to protect wine from external factors, offering advantages in terms of oxygen management and cost.&lt;SEP&gt;Screw cap is a type of wine closure that is being studied for its suitability for long-term wine aging, particularly for its performance with modern liner technology.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08f3f1c8d96e46fade5e0b44bfa52840&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca4e8a21b5cc7aa7758c6cb466cdece6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50be575105a383ed5c7c44e084f7f5df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2eb65b8154604ecd58b709ac758de03&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bf37b81d72a72b3c8a73e22a2f838b6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775588736</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Synthetic Closures">
  <data key="d0">Synthetic Closures</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Synthetic closures are artificial wine stoppers that offer controlled oxygen ingress.&lt;SEP&gt;Synthetic Closures are wine bottle stoppers made from polymers, providing low protection against oxidation but eliminating TCA risk.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08f3f1c8d96e46fade5e0b44bfa52840&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bf37b81d72a72b3c8a73e22a2f838b6</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775588738</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Technical and Micro-Agglomerated Corks">
  <data key="d0">Technical and Micro-Agglomerated Corks</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical and micro-agglomerated corks provide TCA-free performance with controlled oxygen ingress.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08f3f1c8d96e46fade5e0b44bfa52840</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775588738</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bag-in-Box Systems">
  <data key="d0">Bag-in-Box Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Bag-in-box systems are alternative wine packaging formats with significant environmental benefits, despite limitations in shelf life.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08f3f1c8d96e46fade5e0b44bfa52840</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775588740</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Aluminum Cans">
  <data key="d0">Aluminum Cans</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Aluminum cans are used for wine packaging, offering lower carbon footprints but perceived limitations.&lt;SEP&gt;Aluminum Cans are a fast-growing wine packaging segment, often lined with BPANI (Bisphenol A Non-Intent) coatings.&lt;SEP&gt;Aluminum cans used for canned wine are lined with polymer coatings, offering effective oxygen exclusion when properly lined and sealed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08f3f1c8d96e46fade5e0b44bfa52840&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac0e75f96cf1cbcd7ee3984694c2f9ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af38ca1367cf55f446d24669a06d7c24</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775588740</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Carbon Footprint">
  <data key="d0">Carbon Footprint</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The carbon footprint is reduced by 35–84% when using bag-in-box and canned wine formats compared to glass bottles.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08f3f1c8d96e46fade5e0b44bfa52840</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775588741</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Oxygen Transmission Rate (OTR)">
  <data key="d0">Oxygen Transmission Rate (OTR)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Oxygen transmission rate is a measure of the permeability of wine closures to oxygen, affecting wine preservation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08f3f1c8d96e46fade5e0b44bfa52840</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1775588745</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="TCA Contamination">
  <data key="d0">TCA Contamination</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">TCA contamination is a sensory defect associated with natural cork closures, affecting a small percentage of bottled wines.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-08f3f1c8d96e46fade5e0b44bfa52840</data>
