<node id="AWRI">
  <data key="d0">AWRI</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Australian Wine Research Institute (AWRI) provides data on oxygen transfer rates (OTR) of wine closures including synthetic closures.&lt;SEP&gt;The Australian Wine Research Institute (AWRI) conducts closure trials tracking the performance of screw caps compared to natural cork over long periods.&lt;SEP&gt;AWRI is an organization that, along with other researchers, has documented the oxidation and SO₂ depletion in BIB wines.&lt;SEP&gt;The AWRI (Australian Wine Research Institute) conducts ongoing closure trials, representing the gold standard in research for wine aging.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac0e75f96cf1cbcd7ee3984694c2f9ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca4e8a21b5cc7aa7758c6cb466cdece6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50be575105a383ed5c7c44e084f7f5df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bf37b81d72a72b3c8a73e22a2f838b6</data>
