  <data key="d2">Saranex is a type of liner with polyethylene layers covered on both sides with polyvinylidene chloride, known for low oxygen transmission rates.&lt;SEP&gt;Saranex is a liner type used in screw caps, made of polyethylene covered with polyvinylidene chloride, delivering low OTR values.&lt;SEP&gt;Saranex is a modern liner technology used in screw cap and technical closures, necessitating trials to assess its long-term effects on wine aging.</data>
